verbose_text: Four independent variables each significantly influenced ADAMTS-4 levels (all P < 0.001; XREF_TABLE, univariable analysis), namely age (concordance = 0.69; Nagelkerke 's R 2 = 0.10), having OA (concordance = 0.66; Nagelkerke 's R 2 = 0.11), effusion level (concordance = 0.78; Nagelkerke 's R 2 = 0.31) and presence of an inflamed synovium (concordance = 0.68; Nagelkerke 's R 2 = 0.11).
